The paper deals with discrepancy minimization in convex sets, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of linear programming and optimization techniques suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The mention of Gaussian measure and probability suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of numerical analysis (cs.NA).
